WEBVTT

00:08.291 --> 00:10.333
PROFESSOR WILDER: And then,
just like that,

00:10.333 --> 00:11.083
they were kissing.

00:12.000 --> 00:13.291
She didn't know
how they got there.

00:13.667 --> 00:14.875
She had no idea.

00:15.500 --> 00:16.708
The thought of kissing this boy

00:16.708 --> 00:18.875
hadn't crossed her mind
in years.

00:19.375 --> 00:22.000
Which was weird,
because once upon a time,

00:22.000 --> 00:23.542
that was all
she ever thought about.

00:24.834 --> 00:28.792
And then, just like that,
it was over.

00:29.333 --> 00:31.333
He coughed,
she shuffled her feet,

00:32.165 --> 00:33.667
and she laughed
to herself.

00:33.667 --> 00:36.166
It had been one
of those moments,

00:37.000 --> 00:40.291
one of those moments
where you shuck your status
as mere mortal,

00:40.667 --> 00:44.291
and achieve, however briefly,
true greatness.

00:46.417 --> 00:48.834
She had shared many such moments
with this boy,

00:49.708 --> 00:51.208
but now he was leaving

00:51.208 --> 00:54.041
and nothing would ever
be the same again.

00:58.542 --> 01:01.708
So, what do we think
of Joey's story, guys?

01:03.125 --> 01:04.041
Alex?

01:04.041 --> 01:05.583
ALEX: Incredibly banal.

01:05.583 --> 01:07.625
Tell us how you really feel,
Alex, wow!

01:07.625 --> 01:09.000
It's a Hallmark card

01:09.000 --> 01:11.875
about a high school crush.
Who cares?

01:11.875 --> 01:13.166
Well, I thought
it was brilliant.

01:13.166 --> 01:15.708
The way that
she described the moment
leading up to the kiss,

01:15.708 --> 01:17.250
I was right there with her.

01:17.583 --> 01:20.875
It's like Joyce Carol Oates
meets Judy Blume.

01:20.875 --> 01:22.041
You say that
like it's a good thing.

01:22.041 --> 01:24.250
Hey, let's not knock Judy Blume.

01:24.250 --> 01:26.083
Without her, my younger self

01:26.083 --> 01:30.208
would never have
been able to decode
the random acts of madness

01:30.208 --> 01:33.125
perpetrated by that
marvelous creature

01:33.125 --> 01:34.708
known as
the teenage girl.

01:35.083 --> 01:36.166
So, Miss Potter,

01:36.166 --> 01:38.291
I've got some good news
and I've got some bad news.

01:38.291 --> 01:39.417
Good news is,

01:39.417 --> 01:42.542
class is over, today's torture
has come to an end.

01:42.542 --> 01:43.750
Bad news?

01:45.125 --> 01:47.041
You are obviously a writer.

01:49.041 --> 01:51.125
Which means the torture
has just begun.

01:51.417 --> 01:53.166
Alright, everybody,
I will see you next week.

01:53.166 --> 01:56.291
Alex, you're up next.
I can hardly wait.

02:02.917 --> 02:04.333
JOEY: Professor Wilder.

02:04.750 --> 02:07.250
You don't like that "C"
very much, do you, Joey?

02:07.250 --> 02:09.083
No, I don't. In fact, I hate it,

02:09.083 --> 02:10.625
and I was wondering
if there's anything I can do

02:10.625 --> 02:12.125
to make that "C"
a little bit less of a "C"?

02:12.125 --> 02:14.208
Absolutely. You can rewrite it.

02:15.291 --> 02:16.708
How can I do that?

02:17.125 --> 02:19.875
This boy of yours,
does he exist in reality?

02:21.166 --> 02:22.625
He does, actually.

02:22.625 --> 02:23.959
He's coming for a visit
this weekend.

02:23.959 --> 02:24.959
Ah, perfect.

02:25.583 --> 02:27.125
Why is that perfect?

02:27.125 --> 02:28.708
Well, it'll help you
fix your story.

02:29.417 --> 02:31.291
Fix it? I don't even know
what's wrong with it.

02:31.875 --> 02:33.792
The problem with your story,
Joey Potter,

02:33.792 --> 02:36.708
is that it ends at
the very moment it should begin.

02:37.291 --> 02:40.834
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

03:00.000 --> 03:03.000
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

03:46.542 --> 03:51.000
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

04:23.917 --> 04:25.500
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

04:27.542 --> 04:28.083
Hello?

04:28.083 --> 04:30.250
DAWSON: Hey, it's me.

04:30.250 --> 04:32.041
Hey! Are you at the airport?

04:32.041 --> 04:33.875
Um, not exactly, no.

04:34.875 --> 04:36.917
You want the good news
or the bad news first?

04:36.917 --> 04:38.417
Uh oh, not again.

04:38.417 --> 04:39.291
Huh?

04:40.166 --> 04:42.166
[CLEARS THROAT]
Nothing. What is it?

04:42.583 --> 04:45.083
Well, remember the internship
I was telling you about?

04:45.083 --> 04:46.750
The director? You got it?

04:47.083 --> 04:48.000
I did.

04:48.000 --> 04:50.375
Dawson, that's great!
I'm so happy for you.

04:52.959 --> 04:54.708
That means you can't
come for the weekend.

04:56.000 --> 04:57.041
DAWSON: I start today.

04:58.417 --> 04:59.458
Well that sucks.

04:59.458 --> 05:03.500
I know, I was kinda looking
forward to seeing you.

05:04.500 --> 05:06.041
Kind of?

05:06.041 --> 05:07.166
DAWSON: You know what I mean.

05:07.166 --> 05:09.291
Well, I was kinda looking
forward to seeing you, too.

05:10.708 --> 05:11.625
There's always next weekend.

05:11.625 --> 05:13.333
Which will probably turn
into next month.

05:13.333 --> 05:14.708
Or next year.

05:14.708 --> 05:16.417
Before you know it,
it'll be a Christmas Card
every now and then.

05:16.417 --> 05:17.542
When your wife remembers.

05:17.542 --> 05:19.500
We should probably just say
good-bye forever right now.

05:19.500 --> 05:20.708
Yeah, we might as well.

05:21.083 --> 05:22.375
Drama queen.

05:24.291 --> 05:24.792
I know.

05:26.625 --> 05:26.917
Um...

05:28.750 --> 05:30.166
Well, listen, good luck today.

05:30.166 --> 05:32.083
Thanks. And, uh...

05:33.125 --> 05:35.125
I'll call you sometime
over the weekend.

05:38.208 --> 05:38.708
Bye.

05:52.625 --> 05:53.708
[SIGHS]

06:02.458 --> 06:03.708
Good morning, son.

06:03.708 --> 06:05.375
Good morning.
I'm here for an internship.

06:05.875 --> 06:08.041
Is that right?
You have an appointment?

06:08.708 --> 06:09.792
Today's my first day.

06:09.792 --> 06:11.542
First day. You nervous?

06:11.542 --> 06:13.542
Uh, no. Not, uh...

06:14.333 --> 06:16.750
Well, I... Yeah.

06:17.500 --> 06:18.542
What's your last name?

06:18.542 --> 06:20.333
Leery. L, double E, R, Y.

06:22.083 --> 06:24.000
[HONKING]

06:32.208 --> 06:34.667
Do you know where you're going,
Mr. Dawson Leery?

06:34.667 --> 06:36.500
Absolutely no idea.

06:36.500 --> 06:38.917
Straight back, two lefts
and a right.

06:38.917 --> 06:41.417
Ok. Thanks.

06:43.500 --> 06:44.333
Dawson?

06:45.250 --> 06:46.750
Try not to get lost in there.

06:50.166 --> 06:53.792
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

06:58.542 --> 07:00.792
[BELL RINGING]
Heads up.

07:03.250 --> 07:04.750
College guys are hot.

07:04.750 --> 07:07.041
-Give me the phone.
-Why?

07:07.041 --> 07:08.917
'Cause I'm calling Tobey
and telling him you said that.

07:08.917 --> 07:09.834
I can look.

07:09.834 --> 07:12.250
Yeah, but you cannot touch.
I like Tobey.

07:12.250 --> 07:13.708
Tobey's good people.

07:13.708 --> 07:15.083
Yeah, I like Tobey, too.

07:15.917 --> 07:18.583
It just so happens
that we're kinda doomed

07:18.583 --> 07:20.875
to the loneliness
of a long-distance relationship.

07:21.250 --> 07:23.125
Well, that's still better
than the loneliness

07:23.125 --> 07:24.792
of the no-distance relationship.

07:26.959 --> 07:28.625
That doesn't make any sense,
does it?

07:28.625 --> 07:30.083
No, no, it didn't.

07:30.083 --> 07:32.291
Look, you need to get some,
and soon,

07:32.291 --> 07:35.417
alright, before you achieve
born-again virgin status.

07:35.417 --> 07:36.500
Jack.

07:36.500 --> 07:39.041
What? Jen, I'm serious.
It's been far too long.

07:39.041 --> 07:40.083
The last guy
you were with was Henry.

07:40.083 --> 07:42.083
That means last year was
a total wash for you.

07:42.500 --> 07:44.583
Tell me about it.

07:44.583 --> 07:46.333
You know you're a lot more fun
when you're with a guy.

07:46.667 --> 07:48.417
Watching you twist yourself up

07:48.417 --> 07:50.291
into these
little knots of anxiety,

07:50.291 --> 07:51.458
it's highly entertaining.

07:51.792 --> 07:52.750
Thanks. That's good to know.

07:52.750 --> 07:53.583
-It's not in a--
-MAN: Look out!

07:53.583 --> 07:54.291
Oh, heads up!

07:54.792 --> 07:56.125
My goodness!

07:56.125 --> 07:57.792
JACK: Nice throw.

07:57.792 --> 07:58.875
Thanks, man.

07:59.792 --> 08:02.333
Hey, um,
there's a party tonight

08:02.333 --> 08:03.667
over at the Sigma Ep House.

08:03.667 --> 08:05.166
You guys should go,
everything's free.

08:05.166 --> 08:07.375
Punch, beers,
shots, everything.

08:07.917 --> 08:10.208
Cool! Yeah, we'll be there.

08:11.750 --> 08:13.041
Rock on, dude.

08:15.291 --> 08:17.041
"Cool! We'll be there"?

08:17.500 --> 08:20.458
Yeah. Yeah, it'll be fun.

08:20.458 --> 08:21.583
You might meet someone.

08:21.583 --> 08:23.625
Yeah, right. Like I'm gonna meet
the love of my life

08:23.625 --> 08:25.000
at a college frat party?

08:25.875 --> 08:27.208
You didn't think
that guy was hot?

08:27.208 --> 08:29.834
Sure, in a dumb-guy-with-a-dream
kinda way.

08:32.166 --> 08:33.542
Nicely put.

08:50.333 --> 08:51.375
Joey!

08:51.375 --> 08:52.542
Audrey.

08:52.542 --> 08:55.500
Can I ask my favorite roommate
in the whole wide world

08:55.500 --> 08:56.917
the hugest
of all possible favors?

08:58.166 --> 09:01.583
Sure. As long as it doesn't
involve me leaving this room.

09:02.667 --> 09:03.667
[SIGHS]

09:05.000 --> 09:07.208
It involves me leaving
this room, doesn't it?

09:07.208 --> 09:09.000
-Zach is here.
-Where?

09:09.000 --> 09:10.250
Outside.

09:11.834 --> 09:14.083
The one with the tattoo
of his frat on his ankle?

09:14.083 --> 09:15.291
No, that was Tom.

09:15.667 --> 09:16.750
What happened to Tom?

09:16.750 --> 09:18.834
Bad kisser. H.O.B.

09:18.834 --> 09:19.708
H.O.B.?

09:19.708 --> 09:21.000
Hair on back. Gross.

09:21.000 --> 09:22.083
Audrey.

09:22.583 --> 09:23.542
Joey.

09:23.542 --> 09:24.708
We can't go on like this.

09:26.041 --> 09:28.166
Couldn't you just maybe go to
the library for a little while?

09:28.166 --> 09:30.667
Do you have any idea how much
time I've spent sexiled

09:30.667 --> 09:32.875
in the library already
this semester?

09:32.875 --> 09:34.375
It's barely October.

09:34.375 --> 09:35.208
Please?

09:38.000 --> 09:39.667
Pretty please?

09:40.542 --> 09:42.375
And just so you know,
I'm totally planning

09:42.375 --> 09:44.875
on making myself scarce
once your beau gets here.

09:47.208 --> 09:48.542
First of all, he's not my beau.

09:48.542 --> 09:50.417
And second of all,
he's not coming.

09:50.750 --> 09:51.750
Dunston's not coming--

09:51.750 --> 09:52.959
Dawson!

09:52.959 --> 09:54.000
Right.

09:55.041 --> 09:56.250
Something came up.

09:56.583 --> 09:59.875
Hey, do you need me
right now?

09:59.875 --> 10:02.458
because if you need me,
I will totally get rid of Zach.

10:02.458 --> 10:04.125
I mean, you may not
be aware of this yet,

10:04.125 --> 10:06.291
but I'm pretty awesome
like that.

10:09.417 --> 10:10.959
That's ok.

10:10.959 --> 10:13.250
I have to go talk
to Professor Wilder anyway.

10:13.250 --> 10:14.959
And that's what you're wearing?

10:15.959 --> 10:17.625
What's that supposed to mean?

10:17.959 --> 10:21.583
Joey, Professor Wilder
is gorgeous!

10:22.083 --> 10:24.208
Audrey, I'm going
to see him about a paper,

10:24.208 --> 10:25.834
not to hit on him.

10:28.625 --> 10:33.417
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

10:39.792 --> 10:41.625
Is this all
for Professor Wilder?

10:41.625 --> 10:44.792
Mm-hmm. And worth every minute,
if you ask me.

10:48.125 --> 10:54.959
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

11:06.250 --> 11:07.291
Busted.

11:08.166 --> 11:09.458
What are you doing?

11:09.458 --> 11:10.667
Escaping the hordes.

11:11.708 --> 11:13.959
You don't understand.
I could be there for hours.

11:14.542 --> 11:15.834
Must be nice.

11:15.834 --> 11:16.959
What do you mean?

11:16.959 --> 11:19.333
Having freshmen girls
swoon over you all the time.

11:19.333 --> 11:20.333
Oh, don't worry.

11:20.333 --> 11:22.708
I go home and have the wife
and kid bitch me out

11:22.708 --> 11:24.750
for a couple of hours.
Keeps me grounded.

11:26.166 --> 11:28.375
So I presume
you wanted to see me?

11:28.375 --> 11:30.291
Yeah, I wanted to ask you
about my story.

11:30.291 --> 11:31.333
Well, if you must.

11:32.250 --> 11:33.959
If you must ruin
a perfectly glorious day

11:33.959 --> 11:35.667
with a question
about schoolwork,

11:35.667 --> 11:36.834
go right ahead.

11:38.041 --> 11:40.208
Well, you said that the story
should start where it ended,

11:40.208 --> 11:42.375
but the problem is nothing
happened after that.

11:42.708 --> 11:45.125
I mean, the two people just went
their separate ways.

11:45.125 --> 11:46.500
It doesn't matter.

11:46.500 --> 11:47.917
Where do you want
the story to go?

11:49.667 --> 11:52.875
See, writing is about
making choices, Joey,

11:52.875 --> 11:53.875
and you copped out.

11:53.875 --> 11:56.166
You stopped before
you had to make a choice.

11:57.375 --> 11:59.458
I mean, I don't even
know what the kiss meant.

12:02.083 --> 12:03.708
It was just a kiss.

12:03.708 --> 12:06.458
That doesn't mean anything
to me. Make a choice.

12:06.458 --> 12:07.875
What was it, was it...

12:07.875 --> 12:11.667
Sweet? Was it friendly?
Was it passionate?

12:11.667 --> 12:13.875
Was it I wanna lay you
down on the nearest flat surface

12:13.875 --> 12:16.250
and do ungodly things
to you, or...

12:16.708 --> 12:18.083
Was it good-bye?

12:29.375 --> 12:32.583
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

13:06.417 --> 13:07.875
I'll be right back.

13:09.750 --> 13:12.041
Hey, you. Hi.

13:12.041 --> 13:13.291
Hi.

13:13.291 --> 13:14.834
Oh, God. they said
you were young,

13:14.834 --> 13:16.417
but I had no idea.

13:16.417 --> 13:18.250
Weren't you at Kate Mantilini's
last week?

13:18.250 --> 13:20.083
No? Cafe des Artistes, then?

13:20.083 --> 13:22.458
You were with Greg and Mickey
and those UTA guys.

13:22.458 --> 13:23.583
No? Ok, forget it.

13:23.583 --> 13:26.458
We don't know each other.
Come in. Something to drink?

13:26.458 --> 13:27.750
Uh, water.

13:27.750 --> 13:28.875
Water!

13:32.291 --> 13:37.792
So, I gotta tell you,
you are a fantastic writer.

13:37.792 --> 13:38.792
Really?

13:39.291 --> 13:40.708
How can you tell?

13:41.125 --> 13:42.583
It's my job, sweetie.

13:42.583 --> 13:44.083
That's what I do.

13:44.083 --> 13:45.166
Ok.

13:45.166 --> 13:47.041
Well, I should tell you,
I'm a huge fan of Todd's,

13:47.041 --> 13:48.583
um, especially his music videos,

13:48.583 --> 13:49.750
that one he did
for Janet Jackson.

13:49.750 --> 13:53.625
Amazing. Todd is
an effing genius.

13:53.625 --> 13:55.792
The leading visualist
of his time, I think.

13:55.792 --> 13:56.708
Well, sure.

13:56.708 --> 13:58.333
The videos were
a great stepping stone,

13:58.333 --> 14:00.333
but now we're
all about features.

14:00.667 --> 14:02.500
He's shooting Damage, Inc.
on the lot right now.

14:02.500 --> 14:04.166
Right, that comes out
next summer, right?

14:04.166 --> 14:05.125
Yeah, that's right.

14:05.125 --> 14:07.834
And it's my job
to find him his next gig.

14:08.333 --> 14:09.959
I'm trying to talk him
into doing

14:09.959 --> 14:12.625
a feature version
of Seventh Heaven.

14:12.625 --> 14:13.208
The TV show?

14:13.208 --> 14:15.417
Yes. What do you think?

14:16.166 --> 14:17.708
Uh, I think that's...

14:18.000 --> 14:19.250
You know, weird.

14:19.250 --> 14:23.208
Exactly. The plan is to do it
with more of a serious edge,

14:23.208 --> 14:25.500
like what they did with
The Brady Bunch Movie.

14:26.125 --> 14:27.917
And that's where you come in.

14:27.917 --> 14:29.041
I don't get it.

14:29.375 --> 14:31.500
David, your sample was perfect.

14:31.500 --> 14:34.000
You have just the right
voice for this project.

14:34.000 --> 14:35.166
Dawson.

14:35.166 --> 14:36.875
-Excuse me?
-My name is Dawson.

14:36.875 --> 14:38.917
-Dawson Hartley?
-Dawson Leery.

14:39.834 --> 14:41.250
Who's Dawson Hartley?

14:41.875 --> 14:43.375
I have no idea.

14:44.542 --> 14:47.375
Oh! Oh, Dawson Leery.

14:47.375 --> 14:49.083
Right, right.

14:49.083 --> 14:51.000
Uh, what have I read of yours?

14:51.000 --> 14:53.667
Probably just my resume.

14:53.667 --> 14:55.417
ASSISTANT:
David Hartley is here.

14:55.834 --> 14:56.959
Ashley?

14:57.583 --> 14:58.708
Uh-huh?

14:59.792 --> 15:00.917
Who is this?

15:02.333 --> 15:04.125
The new intern.

15:09.708 --> 15:11.458
[CHUCKLING]

15:14.041 --> 15:15.542
JACK: What about Bora Bora?

15:15.542 --> 15:16.708
What do we know about Bora Bora?

15:16.708 --> 15:18.083
Is Bora Bora in the Caribbean?

15:18.083 --> 15:20.250
No, French Polynesia.

15:20.250 --> 15:21.542
Maybe he's gone Kurtz.

15:22.083 --> 15:22.792
Kurtz?

15:22.792 --> 15:25.291
Brando. Apocalypse Now.

15:25.583 --> 15:29.417
Yeah, he's become the leader
of this ragtag band

15:29.417 --> 15:32.458
of expatriates
from some tropical island

15:32.458 --> 15:33.625
you can't even find on a map.

15:33.625 --> 15:34.583
[LAUGHING]

15:34.583 --> 15:38.291
Or maybe he's back
in Capeside, or Boston.

15:40.583 --> 15:42.875
Well, wherever Pacey is,
I hope he's happy.

15:42.875 --> 15:45.417
And if I'm lucky, Audrey
is just about finished

15:45.417 --> 15:47.250
with her latest conquest, so...

15:47.250 --> 15:50.041
Sounds like that girl
has a really promising
future in porn.

15:50.041 --> 15:52.375
JACK:
Bow-chicka-bow-bow,
Chicka-bow--

15:52.375 --> 15:54.208
You know what?
You guys laugh, but it's true.

15:54.208 --> 15:55.708
I open the door,
and I never know

15:55.708 --> 15:56.875
what kind of seedy
little vignette

15:56.875 --> 15:57.792
I'm about to walk into.

15:57.792 --> 15:59.875
Yeah, it's pretty much
the same thing here.

15:59.875 --> 16:02.583
You never know
who Grams is gonna
bring home from bingo.

16:02.583 --> 16:05.083
[CHUCKLES]

16:05.083 --> 16:07.291
So can we count on you tonight
or what?

16:07.291 --> 16:09.458
Mmm... I don't know,

16:09.458 --> 16:11.583
I mean, are we frat party
kind of people?

16:11.583 --> 16:12.917
Is there any past evidence

16:12.917 --> 16:14.792
of us functioning well
at these kind of events?

16:14.792 --> 16:17.125
Which is precisely
why we should go.

16:17.125 --> 16:19.500
Look, it's a new year, guys. Ok?

16:19.500 --> 16:21.792
And we need to,
we need to spread our wings,

16:21.792 --> 16:23.291
challenge any
preconceived notions

16:23.291 --> 16:24.458
we had of college.

16:24.458 --> 16:27.250
And most importantly,
we need to reinvent ourselves.

16:28.083 --> 16:28.959
[LAUGHS]

16:28.959 --> 16:30.166
What's gotten into him?

16:30.166 --> 16:31.834
A cute boy invited him.

16:33.166 --> 16:34.458
-JOEY: Bye.
