Trying to live life.

31:54.834 --> 31:56.375
You know, and have fun.

31:57.375 --> 31:59.083
And...

32:00.333 --> 32:03.125
If I feel like kissing
some boy...

32:04.375 --> 32:06.083
Then so be it.

32:07.250 --> 32:08.375
Exactly.

32:10.041 --> 32:11.291
No regrets.

32:19.417 --> 32:22.291
AUDREY: This was a really
good conversation, Joey Potter.

32:23.208 --> 32:24.625
Hope there's more to come.

32:25.750 --> 32:26.875
JOEY: Me, too.

32:28.375 --> 32:29.542
[KNOCKING]

32:31.417 --> 32:32.750
JOEY: Just a sec.

32:36.792 --> 32:38.208
Hey, Dawson. It's me.

32:38.208 --> 32:40.417
Um, I wanted to call you.

32:40.417 --> 32:43.333
I'm-- I'm at this party
with Jack and Jen

32:43.333 --> 32:45.208
and my crazy roommate,
and guess what?

32:45.208 --> 32:47.125
I'm-- I'm having
a pretty great time.

32:47.125 --> 32:51.667
But as great as it is,
it's not completely great,
and that's because of you.

32:51.667 --> 32:53.500
You're not here,
and I know I said that it was ok

32:53.500 --> 32:55.250
that you didn't come
this weekend, but you know what?

32:55.250 --> 32:58.041
It's not ok,
because I miss you, and...

32:58.041 --> 32:59.917
There was this guy tonight,
and he was hitting on me,

32:59.917 --> 33:01.792
or at least, I think
he was hitting on me,

33:01.792 --> 33:04.291
and he was perfectly nice,
and I just, I blew him off,

33:04.291 --> 33:08.333
and I'm not even sure why,
but I'm pretty sure
it's because of you, and...

33:08.333 --> 33:09.959
I've spent
these past couple of months

33:09.959 --> 33:11.333
acting like you
were just gonna show up

33:11.333 --> 33:13.625
outside of my door one day,
but you're not.

33:13.625 --> 33:15.625
You are out there
following your dream,

33:15.625 --> 33:16.959
which is what
I want for you, Dawson--

33:16.959 --> 33:18.375
[KNOCKING]
BOY: Hurry up! Come on!

33:18.375 --> 33:19.375
In a minute!

33:22.834 --> 33:25.667
Dawson, I think
it's time that...

33:25.667 --> 33:26.875
I let you go.

33:27.667 --> 33:29.166
And it's really hard
for me to do,

33:29.166 --> 33:32.000
because I know
that there's a part of me

33:32.000 --> 33:36.000
that's gonna be in love with you
for the rest of my life, but...

33:36.333 --> 33:38.834
You know, this running in place
and this daydreaming,

33:38.834 --> 33:41.000
it's just not healthy
for either of us.

33:41.000 --> 33:43.834
And so, this is me
cutting the cord.

33:43.834 --> 33:47.083
This is me doing what I should
have done three months ago.

33:48.667 --> 33:50.458
I'm saying
good-bye, Dawson.

33:53.125 --> 33:54.083
Uh...

33:55.500 --> 33:56.917
Call me back.

33:57.792 --> 33:59.041
Bye.

34:38.166 --> 34:39.500
Ah, no.

34:40.208 --> 34:41.333
No what?

34:41.333 --> 34:43.500
No, not interested.

34:43.500 --> 34:46.500
[CHUCKLES]
"No, not interested"
in what?

34:47.417 --> 34:50.083
In whatever it is that
you're selling, pal.

34:50.083 --> 34:51.917
Ok, I didn't even say anything.

34:52.250 --> 34:53.708
Well, you were about to.

34:54.250 --> 34:55.458
I was?

34:55.458 --> 34:58.792
Yeah. You were about to give me
your best opening line.

34:58.792 --> 35:01.959
Something like, "Hey, girl."

35:01.959 --> 35:04.375
Which, word to the wise,
is neither clever nor charming,

35:04.375 --> 35:05.750
and then you were probably gonna

35:05.750 --> 35:06.917
follow it up
with the perennial classic,

35:06.917 --> 35:10.083
"Hey, you know what would look
really good on you? Me."

35:10.083 --> 35:11.125
[LAUGHS]

35:12.291 --> 35:14.458
Wow. People actually say stuff
like that in real life?

35:14.458 --> 35:15.708
[GRUNTS]

35:16.208 --> 35:19.250
Well, just so you know,
I'm not that guy.

35:19.250 --> 35:21.250
Look, for all I know,
you could be the kind of guy

35:21.250 --> 35:22.917
who cruises frat parties

35:22.917 --> 35:24.792
because he knows
that he can capitalize

35:24.792 --> 35:26.708
on the significant dearth
of sensitive types,

35:26.708 --> 35:28.959
which is even worse, man,
'cause it's sneaky.

35:29.625 --> 35:32.750
Ok, A, you're crazy.

35:32.750 --> 35:34.542
Which is not
entirely unappealing.

35:34.542 --> 35:35.959
And B,

35:36.291 --> 35:38.041
I'm not that guy, either.

35:39.291 --> 35:41.125
Well, then,
what are you doing here?

35:41.125 --> 35:42.333
I'm in the band.

35:43.625 --> 35:46.542
We got paid 50 bucks to play,
and 50 bucks is 50 bucks, lady.

35:48.000 --> 35:49.375
Oh...

35:49.375 --> 35:51.542
You guys,
you guys were actually good.

35:52.250 --> 35:53.583
Thank you.

35:55.000 --> 35:56.875
Ok, so what, pray tell,
are you doing here,
little Miss Know-It-All?

35:56.875 --> 35:58.625
I mean, besides making a sport

35:58.625 --> 36:00.333
out of scowling
into your beer there.

36:00.333 --> 36:01.500
[LAUGHS]

36:02.959 --> 36:05.875
-Hey, scowling can be fun.
-CHARLIE: [LAUGHS]

36:06.291 --> 36:07.959
Well, look,
I gotta go pack up my gear.

36:07.959 --> 36:10.667
It was wonderful sharing
this moment with you.

36:11.000 --> 36:11.959
Really.

36:17.166 --> 36:19.333
Look, just so you know, alright?

36:19.333 --> 36:21.834
All I was gonna say was,
"Hi, my name's Charlie,

36:21.834 --> 36:23.041
What's yours?"

36:23.041 --> 36:24.208
That's all.

36:25.375 --> 36:27.000
And then, I was kind of hoping
maybe we'd talk a little,

36:27.000 --> 36:28.500
and I'd find out
that you're the kind of girl

36:28.500 --> 36:31.166
who doesn't usually
come to parties like these,

36:31.166 --> 36:35.834
and that would explain why the
cutest girl in the whole place

36:35.834 --> 36:37.750
is alone by herself
in the corner.

36:38.667 --> 36:42.208
Because you're right, most
of the guys here are creeps.

36:43.166 --> 36:45.000
And the girls are even worse.

36:45.000 --> 36:47.500
And God,
I hope they don't procreate.

36:47.875 --> 36:49.166
But they will.

36:50.291 --> 36:52.208
And we're just gonna
have to do our best

36:52.208 --> 36:53.250
and fight the good fight.

36:54.542 --> 36:56.750
And make sure their kind
doesn't take over the world.

36:59.542 --> 37:00.708
That's all.

37:05.542 --> 37:06.542
Charlie?

37:09.792 --> 37:10.792
Jen.

37:11.208 --> 37:13.333
Uh, my, my name's Jen.

37:15.333 --> 37:17.041
Well, it's nice
to meet you, Jen.

37:19.375 --> 37:21.000
I'm sorry.

37:24.917 --> 37:26.333
What are you so smiley about?

37:28.542 --> 37:29.500
Shut up.

37:29.500 --> 37:30.750
[LAUGHS] Yeah.

37:42.041 --> 37:43.375
So...

37:43.375 --> 37:45.291
How'd your first day go?

37:45.708 --> 37:46.708
[SIGHS]

37:47.125 --> 37:48.417
First and last, actually.

37:48.417 --> 37:53.583
I just got fired from a job
that doesn't even pay anything.

37:54.083 --> 37:57.250
Well, there are worse things.

38:00.667 --> 38:02.542
Not at the moment, there aren't.

38:03.708 --> 38:05.500
Where are you from, kid?

38:06.542 --> 38:08.625
I'm from, uh, Capeside.

38:08.625 --> 38:10.667
It's a small town
in Massachusetts.

38:10.667 --> 38:12.750
Ok, sure.
I'm from Boston originally.

38:12.750 --> 38:14.166
-Really?
-GUARD: Yeah.

38:15.000 --> 38:16.917
All my friends are
in Boston right now.

38:16.917 --> 38:19.000
GUARD: How come
you're not with them?

38:19.959 --> 38:21.708
'Cause this was a dream.

38:22.625 --> 38:23.500
Movies.

38:26.917 --> 38:28.959
How's it matching up
against the reality?

38:33.083 --> 38:35.291
It's weird. It, uh...

38:35.291 --> 38:36.583
It doesn't.

38:37.834 --> 38:39.708
Why don't I call you a cab?

38:41.583 --> 38:42.959
Thanks.

38:44.750 --> 38:51.041
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

39:00.708 --> 39:03.875
Ok, Jen.
You gonna tell me his name,

39:03.875 --> 39:05.458
or am I gonna have to kill you?

39:05.458 --> 39:06.792
Shh-shh-shh-shh.

39:06.792 --> 39:09.166
Let's try and not wake
the dragon lady here.

39:12.000 --> 39:13.166
Jen...

39:14.125 --> 39:15.667
Jen...

39:16.834 --> 39:19.792
Charlie, ok?
His name is Charlie.

39:22.000 --> 39:23.542
Charlie's cute.

39:23.542 --> 39:24.417
Whatever.

39:24.417 --> 39:26.708
In a dumb-guy-with-a-dream
kind of way.

39:26.708 --> 39:27.959
Charlie's not dumb.

39:27.959 --> 39:29.625
Oh, someone's smitten.

39:29.625 --> 39:31.291
Would you shut up?

39:31.291 --> 39:35.291
Oh, man, if there are cookies
in these cupboards,

39:35.291 --> 39:38.208
I will devote my life
to God and His teachings.

39:38.208 --> 39:41.000
Oh, music to my ears, Jennifer.

39:41.375 --> 39:42.250
Sorry, Grams.

39:42.250 --> 39:43.166
-Sorry.
-Sorry.

39:43.166 --> 39:46.208
Oh, nonsense.
I can sleep when I'm dead.

39:46.458 --> 39:48.834
So, how was your party?

39:50.041 --> 39:51.208
Alright.

39:51.208 --> 39:53.041
-JOEY: Jen met a boy.
-JACK: Charlie.

39:53.041 --> 39:54.250
And he's not dumb.

39:55.333 --> 39:58.917
GRAMS: Well, praise the Lord
and pass the sugar.

39:59.708 --> 40:02.542
Well, I'd say it's about time.

40:03.041 --> 40:05.500
-That's nice.
-Thanks.

40:09.708 --> 40:13.208
♪ [MUSIC PLAYS] ♪

41:41.959 --> 41:43.458
[KNOCKING]

41:45.125 --> 41:46.250
Audrey.

41:49.000 --> 41:50.375
Audrey.

41:52.834 --> 41:54.583
[KNOCKING]

42:00.166 --> 42:01.500
Hold on.

42:10.834 --> 42:11.917
Hey.

42:15.000 --> 42:16.208
Hey.

42:56.542 --> 43:03.375
♪ [MUSIC PLAYING] ♪
